Definition: from the Sanskrit word for `knowledge') any of the most ancient sacred writings of Hinduism written in early Sanskrit
Example: traditionally believed to comprise the Samhitas, the Brahmanas, the Aranyakas, and the Upanishads
Synonyms: Veda, noun, person, vedist, sacred_text, cognition, Hinduism, c, communication, Sanskrit, from, the, word, for, knowledge, any, of, most, ancient, sacred, writings, written, in, early, traditionally, believed, to, comprise, Samhitas, Brahmanas, Aranyakas, and, Upanishads
Category: noun.communication
